@mhegazy I totally dropped this PR on the floor after something else came up, but thank you for fixing that export.  You're right this doesn't look totally correct.

[The documentation doesn't mention](https://github.com/chalk/supports-color#usage) the `supportsColor: [Function: getSupportLevel]` function, so I left it out.  This typing just exports the two properties `stdout` & `stderr`, which I assumed would be similar to the default export of an object with the same properties.

Can you clarify what you would prefer to see here?

